      "edited_at": "2025-07-03T08:29:53.409Z",
      "content": "<p>\u2026automatically picks the newest image file in that directory.</p><p>Securely, robustly updating a whole service config consisting of many files by just dropping in a single file, that&#39;s awesome, no? At least in PoV that&#39;s quite an improvement over traditional configuration management schemes!</p><p>Note that the confext stack is refreshed *before* the actual reload of the service happens, i.e. before ExecReload= is run or SIGHUP are sent, to ensure that the service sees the update by then.</p>",
